    • Method Detail

      • findIncomeTaxPeriod

        @Cacheable(value="incomeTaxPeriods")
 @Query(value="SELECT incomeTaxPeriod FROM IncomeTaxPeriod incomeTaxPeriod WHERE incomeTaxPeriod.startDate <= :paymentStartDate AND incomeTaxPeriod.endDate >= :paymentStartDate")
java.util.Optional<IncomeTaxPeriod> findIncomeTaxPeriod(@Param(value="paymentStartDate")
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  java.time.LocalDate paymentStartDate)
        Finds the correct income tax period and its related tax rates based on a date in between the start and the end of a tax period.

        This method is using spring cache in order to cache the income tax period and its eagerly fetched tax rates.

        The related tax rates will be returned order by the tax rate start amount ascending (nulls being first)

        Parameters:
        paymentStartDate - the payment start date indicating the payment period and tax period
        Returns:
        the income tax period for the supplied payment start date
        See Also:
        IncomeTaxPeriod
